@node newicon_mode "NewIcon mode"

             (Ÿ`Ṗ._.Ṗ' Mr Icon `Ṗ._.Ṗ'Ÿ)


           (_.Ṗ'Ÿ`Ṗ NewIcon mode Ṗ'Ÿ`Ṗ._)

If you have the newicon.library present in your
system. An additional checkbox shall appear in
the bottom of the window.

When the NewIcon checkbox is checked you will
not be able to modify any normal icons. If an
object has both a NewIcon AND an ordinary one -
only the NewIcon will be modified.

Note:
    If you have NewIcons running and you copy a
    normal icon to an object who has a Newicon
    the NewIcon will remain as the icons image.

    The normal icon you copied will be visible
    if you disable NewIcons.

@endnode


@node window "The window"

             (Ÿ`Ṗ._.Ṗ' Mr Icon `Ṗ._.Ṗ'Ÿ)


            (_.Ṗ'Ÿ`Ṗ The window Ṗ'Ÿ`Ṗ._)

The window contains:

    Two drop-boxes.

    Click inside a dropbox to activate the Source or Destination

      o @{b}Source@{ub}
        The source icon.
        The icon that shall be copied

      o @{b}Destination@{ub}
        The destination icon.
        The object the icon shall be copied to


    Gadgets:
        o @{b} Copy @{ub}
          Copy the source image to the destination

        o @{b} Swap @{ub}
          Change the places of source and destination

        o @{b} Delete @{ub}
          Delete the icon in the active dropbox (Source or Destination)

        o @{b} Create @{ub}
          Create a default icon for the icon in the
          active dropbox.

        o @{b} Browse @{ub}
          Choose icon image for the active dropbox by a filerequester

        o @{bg shine}  @{bg back}  NewIcon mode
          Toggle between NewIcon mode and normal mode.


    Appwindow:
        Drop icons in the dropboxes to load the image

@endnode
@node startup "MrIcon startup"

             (Ÿ`Ṗ._.Ṗ' Mr Icon `Ṗ._.Ṗ'Ÿ)


            (_.Ṗ'Ÿ`Ṗ The Startup Ṗ'Ÿ`Ṗ._)


o TOOLTYPES
  In the MrIcon icon you can place the following
  tooltypes:

    FONT=<fontname>/<size>
        For example:
            @{fg shine}FONT=GHelvetica.font/9@{fg text}

    XPOS=<no>
        The horizontal position of the window
        default is 60

    YPOS=<no>
        The vertical position of the window
        default is 30

    NEWICONMODE=YES/NO
        Shall the "NewIcon mode" checkbox be checked?
        Default is NO

o The CLI/SHELL arguments are the same as the tooltypes.

    @{b}FONT/K,NEWICONMODE/S,XPOS/N/K,YPOS/N/K@{ub}

    Examples:
        1> @{fg shine}MrIcon FONT=topaz.font/11 NEWICONMODE YPOS=67@{fg text}

        2> @{fg shine}MrIcon NEWICONMODE@{fg text}



@endnode
