@node popups "Popups"

             (Ÿ`Ṗ._.Ṗ' Mr Icon `Ṗ._.Ṗ'Ÿ)


            (_.Ṗ'Ÿ`Ṗ The popups Ṗ'Ÿ`Ṗ._)

Click in one of the dropboxes with your right mouse button.
A small listview will now take the dropbox's place.

This listview can be filled with external programs that
you can launch. For example if you'd like to edit the loaded icon
in a iconeditor or convert the icon's color.

You can configure these listviews by editing the file tools.mri in
the MrIcon drawer.

The lines in the file is built up like this:
@{fg shine}"Name" "CLI/SHELL line to be executed" [IFICON] [ONLYNEWICON] [ONLYNORMAL]@{fg text}


Name         The name that will appear in the listview
             If it contains spaces then place in in quotes.

CLI/SHELL    The CLI/SHELL command line that will launch a
             program.  This line can include following tags:

             %C - active icon name
             %c - active icon name without ".info"
             %S - source icon name
             %s - source icon name without ".info"
             %D - destination icon name
             %d - destination icon name without ".info"

             Example:
             @{fg shine}"Run >NIL: sys:tools/Iconian/Iconian %c"@{fg text}

IFICON       If this optional argument is used then the listview-label
             will only be available if an icon is loaded into the
             program.

ONLYNEWICON  If this optional argument is used then the listview-label
             will only be available if the @{"NewIcon mode" link newicon_mode} is enabled.

ONLYNORMAL   If this optional argument is used then the listview-label
             will only be available if the @{"NewIcon mode" link newicon_mode} is disabled.




Included tools:
    deftool   By David Lidström
              A tiny, simple program to change an icon's default tool
              argument: the icon's name without ".info"

    comment   By David Lidström
              Another small, simple program to change file comments
              argument: the icon's name without ".info"


@endnode





